content.description:
Western Rust is a complete problem that traverses a slight overhang via fun movement, on perfect edges, over a great landing.

Sit start with a left hand edge and a right hand jug (same start as

Bloktrotter

). From there, move out left to an edge, then make a burly right hand move to a sharp (crux?) but good edge. At that point, bump the left through a pair of sidepulls, adjust the feet, fall into a pinch/edge (crux?), work further left to the jug rail (start hold of Points On The Package), then pull up to a left hand edge, get a high right foot, and work the remaining edges to reach a solid topout.
content.protection: A few pads should do it, the entire landing is very good.
content.location:
It shares the same start as

Bloktrotter

, traverses left, and finishes up Point On The Package.

content.description: Sit start with hands matched on the jug. From there, move to a good left hand edge, edge high with the right foot, work the remaining edges, and top it out.
content.protection: A pad or two is good, the landing is very good.
content.location: Ascend the center-west face of Overhills Boulder.

content.description:
Bloktrotter climbs a slightly overhung face on perfectly oxidized, Dakota sandstone edges.

Sit start with a left hand sidepull and a right hand jug. From there, reach out left to crimp, then make a big right hand to move to a perfect edge (crux), continue out left to a sidepull, set the feet, and stand up tall to a right hand gaston which accesses a good left hand crimp and an easy top out.
content.protection: A pair of pads should do it, the landing is very good.
content.location: It ascends the west face of Overhills Boulder.
